Tharaka Nithi Deputy Governor Eliud Mureithi's bodyguard allegedly stole his Sh3.5 million on Tuesday night.A source said Mate had just arrived at his home in Kinoru when the Administration Police officer assigned to his security detail turned against him.It is said that constable Josephat Kipyegon confronted the Deputy Governor and grabbed the suitcase which had the cash.The source said Mureithi had just sold his piece of land at Kathwana in Tharaka Nithi and was planning to bank the money on Wednesday."The two struggled but the bodyguard from Marimanti South AP camp removed his pistol and aimed at the Deputy Governor who had to run safety," the source said.The officer is said to have left his shoe behind while escaping with the cash. Flying Squad officers and a team from the DCI visited the scene.Eastern region police commander Gideon Amalla said they launched a search for the police officer.He said the DG was not with his personal driver at the time of the robbery.